external_knowledge:
- 'Golden goose' refers to a source of great wealth or prosperity;
- Revenue is calculated by multiplying the course price by the amount paid by the student;
- The course price is stored as a string in the format "$1,234.56".

- 'Average Course Revenue' refers to the mean of the total revenues generated by all courses;
- 'Total Location Capacity' is the sum of all capacities across all locations;
- 'Popular Courses' are courses that fall into a specific category designated as popular;
- 'Most Popular Instructor Specialization' is the specialization area that has the highest number of instructors.

- "blossomed with the fruits of student enthusiasm" refers to the total number of registrations for each course;
- "across all schedules" indicates that the registration count includes all schedules associated with each course;
- The `course_id` is the unique identifier for each course.

- "highest peak" refers to the maximum value of total registrations;
- "landscape of course popularity" refers to the distribution of student registrations across different courses;
- "embarked on the journey of learning" refers to students who have registered for a course.

- "registrations count" refers to the number of students enrolled in courses within each category;
- "total revenue" is calculated by summing the amount paid by students and subtracting any refunds;
- "average payment" is the average amount paid by students after accounting for any refunds.

- "most lucrative" refers to the courses that have generated the highest total revenue;
- "measured by the total revenue they generate" means the sum of all payments made by students for each course;
- "how many students have registered" refers to the total number of registrations for each course.

- "educators" refers to instructors;
- "assigned to guide the educational journey" refers to being associated with schedules;
- "in alphabetical order" means the results are sorted by the instructor's name.

- "blooming" refers to courses that are popular and have multiple registrations;
- "not fully filled" refers to courses that have available seats;
- "reaped some financial harvest" refers to courses that have generated revenue.

- 'Gardens' represent courses;
- 'Gardeners' represent instructors;
- 'Plots of land' represent locations;
- 'Spots left for new plants' represent available seats;
- 'Open for registration' means the course has at least one registered student;
- 'Closed for registration' means the course has no registered students.
